  "text": "Behavioral and neuroendocrine response to swim stress The forced swim test was conducted as previously described (Boyce-Rustay and Holmes 2006; [CITATION_1] . The apparatus was a transparent Plexiglas cylinder (20 cm diameter) filled halfway with water (24±1°C) into which mice were gently lowered. The mouse was given a 6-min trial and returned to the home cage. The presence/absence of immobility (cessation of limb movements except minor involuntary movements of the hind limbs) was manually observed using an instantaneous sampling technique every 5 s during the last 4 min and expressed as a percentage of total observations during the period.",
